  "title": "feat(InfiniteHits): add new widget",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for submitting a pull request!\r\n  Please provide enough information so that others can review your pull request.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n_Note : if the PR gets approved, commits will be squashed into 1 before merging_\r\n\r\n@bobylito feel free to assign other reviewers on this one!\r\n\r\n## Summary\r\nAfter hearing many requests for a showMore/infiniteHits widget and given the fact that this feature exists in `React-Instantsearch`, @bobylito helped me bring it to `Instantsearch.js`! 🎉  🍾  🔎 \r\n\r\nThe **InfiniteHits widget** should be used as a replacement for the regular Hits widget, _not_ along with it.\r\nIt will replicate the Hits widget API and rendering and add a button at the bottom that is customizable with a label and CSS classes.\r\nThis widget shouldn't be used with the pagination widget since the 2 features overlap.\r\n\r\n<!--\r\n  Explain the **motivation** for making this change.\r\n  What existing problem does the pull request solve?\r\n  Are there any linked issues?\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## Result\r\nYou can try the widget here: [demo](http://infinitehits.surge.sh)\r\n\r\nGIF preview:\r\n\r\n![2017-02-09 15_28_54](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4720300/22787403/84c8261a-eedc-11e6-9715-5520acaf1e8a.gif)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<!--\r\n  Demonstrate the code is solid.\r\n  Example: The exact commands you ran and their output,\r\n  screenshots / videos if the pull request changes UI.\r\n-->\r\n",
